Class CollectionAssertion<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • testHelp.ObjectAssertion
      • testHelp.CollectionAssertion<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of object the collection contains

    public class CollectionAssertion<T>
extends ObjectAssertion
    Represents an assertion about a collection, like an array or ArrayList.

      • isEquivalentTo

        public CollectionAssertion<T> isEquivalentTo(java.util.Collection<T> other)
        Verifies that this collection contains the same objects as the specified one, regardless of order, using the Object.equals method to check for equivalence of elements.

        Note that currently the implementation does not handle the case where the collection contains different numbers of the same object.
